TO ADDRESS SOME QUESTIONS I AM ANTICIPATING: 

1. Dresden is a town near where I live. It has nothing to do with the Dresden Files.

2. No, I did not have the Foundation turn a bunch of kids into D-class because of teh grimdark. I put myself in a place where the Foundation was faced with an influx of something conspicuously anomalous (identical children are fairly easy to spot), plentiful, and that the Foundation could not stop the influx of. The Foundation must hide these children from view; you can't just stick a bunch of identical children in orphanages around the world when they keep coming; that solution's not practical in the long run. The way I saw it, the Foundation's only options were a)give all of the children plastic surgery and amnestic treatment and throw them into the foster system or something similarly dismissive, which would be fairly expensive and complex; b) raise all of the children to adulthood, which would be expensive, labor intensive, and would raise complex issues when the 1680 clones came to adulthood (they're still clones, sotrain them as researchers? What if they don't want to? What if they freak out when they see more of themselves?) c) kill all of the children immediately, or d) use the children as D-class. The latter option keeps them hidden in Foundation facilities, gets use out of them (do you think the Foundation isn't pragmatic?), and may or may not result in their being far fewer of them over time.

I don't like the idea of the Foundation brainwashing and killing children, but life has always been fairly cheap to Overwatch, and I don't see a better option.

3. Nothing offensive is meant by the use of a short bus. I just liked that particular picture.







